{"title":"E. 2-Coloring","contestId":"1503","contestName":"Codeforces Round #712 (Div. 1)","problemIndex":"E","timeLimit":"3 seconds","memLimit":"256 megabytes","inputFormat":"standard input","outputFormat":"standard output","problemHtml":"<p>There is a grid with $$$n$$$ rows and $$$m$$$ columns. Every cell of the grid should be colored either blue or yellow.</p><p>A coloring of the grid is called stupid if every row has exactly one segment of blue cells and every column has exactly one segment of yellow cells.</p><p>In other words, every row must have at least one blue cell, and all blue cells in a row must be consecutive. Similarly, every column must have at least one yellow cell, and all yellow cells in a column must be consecutive.</p><p></p><center> <img class=\"tex-graphics\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/269b01ee0ca84f0b74c1a7220d58280b61d115fe.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"> An example of a stupid coloring. </center><p></p><p></p><center> <img class=\"tex-graphics\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/1898235ec8e6365798d3e59b27975ed7b774aaa4.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"> Examples of clever colorings. The first coloring is missing a blue cell in the second row, and the second coloring has two yellow segments in the second column. </center><p></p><p>How many stupid colorings of the grid are there? Two colorings are considered different if there is some cell that is colored differently.</p>","inSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Input</div><p>The only line contains two integers $$$n$$$, $$$m$$$ ($$$1\\le n, m\\le 2021$$$).</p>","outSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Output</div><p>Output a single integer â€” the number of stupid colorings modulo $$$998244353$$$.</p>","noteHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Note</div><p>In the first test case, these are the only two stupid $$$2\\times 2$$$ colorings.</p><p></p><center> <img class=\"tex-graphics\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/7faa5efe911c5dccfb095ae05af65d6a0980943a.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"> </center><p></p>","sampleTestcases":[{"id":1617463242991,"input":"2 2\n","output":"2\n"},{"id":1617463242992,"input":"4 3\n","output":"294\n"},{"id":1617463242993,"input":"2020 2021\n","output":"50657649\n"}],"submitUrl":"https://codeforces.com/contest/1503/submit","language":"c++"}